##"Drug Hunter" : behind the circulation of "patient number one" in Shanghai

Micro Signal Xinminzhoukan

Function description, depth and angle —— this is what we can do.

In many cases, unlike doctors, patients will volunteer as much useful information as they can to the doctor. Migrant workers said they hope that after the outbreak, the public can understand the importance of the transfer, for their future work to provide more convenience.

Reporter | Ying Chen

Shanghai's "patient zero" has lifted the veil of mystery as people talk about the new pneumonia.

According to the report, the telephone of Shanghai CDC rang at 5 pm on January 16. The call came from the Changning District Center for Disease Control, a hospital in Changning District, where a patient from Wuhan, highly suspected of new pneumonia.

Two doctors from the Emergency Transmission Department of the Shanghai Center for Disease Control and Prevention rushed to the fever clinic of the hospital, waiting for the nucleic acid test results, while beginning the intense flow of work. To the relief of the migrant workers, the first confirmed patient in Shanghai was very cooperative. After arriving in Shanghai, he had not visited any other places. The only close contacts were his daughter and her son-in-law. His daughter's family also drove him to the hospital for treatment, there's no public transportation involved.

On January 20, the city's first new coronary patient was confirmed after a national review.

In the words of Pan Hao, deputy director of the Shanghai CDC's new pneumonia prevention and control field working group, the role of circulation is to control the increase.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The Silkworm, or epidemiological survey, IS THE SEARCH FOR INFECTIOUS IN & Out through the intricacies of life, by stringing together seemingly unrelated pieces in a tightly linked chain of infection, then by isolating the source of infection, cut off the means of transmission and other measures to protect vulnerable groups. At the same time, the survey also provides a basis for determining the source of infection and close contacts of the case.

All by the hospital initially identified suspected patients, the flow of personnel must be the first time intervention, even if the final discovery is "false alarm. ". Therefore, some netizens gave the migrants a cool nickname: drug hunter.

In fact, it was the in-depth investigation and investigation of more than 2,500 suspected cases of new coronary pneumonia in Shanghai by the mobile staff, as well as the investigation of possible clues of infection and mode of transmission, that isolated the source of infection and cut off the transmission route in the first place, as far as possible to control the new coronavirus this "spark. ".

It is worth mentioning that one third of the more than 330 confirmed cases in Shanghai to date have been confirmed in close contacts. This also confirms the importance of the flow, as well as the prevention and control of Shanghai is effective.

To help people find their memories and fill in their timelines

"Our phones are on 24 hours a day, ready to go to the scene. On the night of shift change, I couldn't sleep deeply. It's not unusual to be woken up by a phone call in the middle of the night,"said Ma Zhaoxiang, who was born in 1990.

Ma Zhaoxiang is a staff member of the Acute Infectious Disease Prevention and Control Section of the Center for Disease Control and Prevention in Jing 'an district.

"This is the first time I have experienced a major epidemic in my working life. Although I have accumulated some experience in my daily work, to be honest, I feel a little nervous. At work, I constantly remind myself to be careful, not to make mistakes, and to show my professionalism in front of patients,"he told Xinmin Weekly, if he has a difficult problem, he will ask for advice from an experienced colleague.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Jingan district CDC staff in the field to carry out the flow of work

At around 1700 hours one day, Ma Zhaoxiang, near the end of his shift, received a call from a hospital in the district, saying that he had received a suspected case of new coronary pneumonia. He didn't have time to eat. He immediately examined the set-up as a medical device -- a protective device, a flow meter, a sampling tube, a sterilizing device, and rushed to the hospital with his colleagues.

The purpose of the study was to answer the key questions of "where the patient was infected, by whom or by what means" and "who might be in close contact with him or her" . Therefore, in the investigation, the flow of personnel to do as much as possible meticulous. Where the suspect had been in the 14 days before the attack, who he had been in close contact with, the number of trips he had taken, and so on, were as detailed as possible.

"But the old Shanghai woman I met at the time was quite confident because she didn't have a history of travel in Wuhan, or any relevant contacts, and didn't think she would get sick. In the face of our drift, we complained for a long time, and the answer was rather perfunctory,"Ma recalled, he tried to tease out as much information as he could as he soothed her. "But the first conversation wasn't very successful, and there was very little useful information. All I know is that she went to two hospitals and had dinner with her daughter and her family. "

Ma Zhaoxiang told the reporter that when they contacted the old lady and her daughter, the other side was also quite vigilant, the first phone call, even names and addresses are not willing to be given, "They would answer the phone, but they wouldn't say anything more. Her daughter was worried that we would come to the house, and didn't want the neighbors pointing out that they would be living here for a long time. ".

Ma Zhaoxiang is doing the flow of the phone

But the next day, the old lady tested positive and was diagnosed with new coronary pneumonia. When the old lady heard the result, the complaint became more of a concern. In his second communication with her, Ma first calmed her down and then told her the gravity of the situation. This time, the old lady cooperated more, said the name of the two outer district hospitals and then looked at the department.

"We suspected at the time that there was a high risk of infection while she was in hospital, but with the help of the city, we ruled it out, " Ma said, in an effort to find the source of the woman's infection, he called her again.

The Old Lady couldn't remember many details because of the long time. Ma Zhaoxiang accompanied her day by day, even to the precise point of time. Therefore, a transfer, usually take two hours is not long.

Finally, the Old Lady recalled that she once went to a trading center with her daughter. "Then we were able to guide her daughter to further contact with the person who was dealing with the patient on the same day that they were dealing with a confirmed case, " Ma said, adding that the source of the Old Lady's infection was now clear, the flow is complete.

I hope the patient will be more cooperative

If you encounter patients who can not remember slowly guide memories, then encounter patients who deliberately conceal, only through the flow of observation and communication personnel to achieve a breakthrough.

Jing 'an district CDC food nutrition and health section chief Chen Yiqiong in the outbreak is one of the flow of support group. In the cases she encountered, she found that many patients described their own or their loved ones'activities in more detail for their own protection, "But when it comes to friends, or distant relatives, out of a variety of concerns, many people are more ambiguous. ".

Chen Yiqiong clearly remembered that she had met an aunt who had just retired when she was doing the tune. Aunt Chen Yiqiong in the guidance of the very co-operation to tell their own trajectory, but when Chen Yiqiong pressed her specific blank time, aunt began to equivocate.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Chen Yiqiong is working on the call flow

After several cross-examination, coupled with from aunt son there inquires, Chen Yi know, aunt originally is about a few little sisters dinner. "Some of these girls may not be very familiar with them, but they are from shopping for food or dancing in the square. By doing mental work for our aunt, we finally got the contact information of one of the sisters, and through her, we were able to track everyone,"says Chen Yi.

In Chen Yiqiong's view, pulling a family routine is a way to get to know and gain trust with the other person quickly. Before asking the other person to recall, she first recalls the details of that day, "If it's a rainy day, I'll remind them that it looks like a rainy day. Have you ever ordered takeout or gone out to get a delivery? "

Jing 'an district center for Disease Control and Prevention of Acute Infectious Diseases Section chief Li Enguo in the review of information

Mobile personnel have their own work principles, more precisely, is the mission. From the moment of notification from the hospital, the first time to produce a report of the initial investigation, almost non-negotiable. Because a minute later, the virus will be in an unnamed place more "happy" one minute.

Most of the time, unlike doctors, patients volunteer as much useful information to doctors as they can. "But we are passive to ask, the more we think about it, the more we can ask about it, " Chen Yi said, adding that he hoped that after the outbreak, the public would understand the importance of it, to make it easier for them to do their jobs.
